abstract: Egypt's Islamist Muslim Brotherhood has launched aggressive campaign to win favor in Cairo's dense Imbaba neighborhood, looking to shore up support before coming parliamentary election.
snippet: Egypt’s parliamentary election may be nearly two months away, but the contest has already begun in the neighborhood of Imbaba, where the arc of the Egyptian revolution is on display.
